  "text": "Jursinic and Pearcy [CITATION_1] Plants used in these experiments were grown from seeds produced by reciprocal crossing of individuals of the commercially available Brassica napus L. varieties 'Regent' and 'Triton' [CITATION_2] . All plants were grown in either a high or low light intensity growth chamber as described earlier [CITATION_3] .",
